widgets_values:
###Before you hit the Queue Prompt Button:

- setup the controlnet models - setup the animatediff models - setup model and lcm lora (if needed) -> checkpoint loader
download the files if you haven't already.



---------------------------->

- Load-Cap: Number of Images to Load.
- Skip First Frames: Skips the number of Frames at start.
- Select every nth: 1 (default) will render every single image. Increase to render every 2nd or 3rd image, but the smoothness of the movment will suffer.
- Overlap: the overlap can be used to render extra frames that can be used to fade the changes between the queues. e.g. load-cap = 200 + 15 overlap will render 215 images each queue. the last 15 frames of the first queue and the first 15 of the next queue are the same. (for external video editing only)
- Queue * Load-Cap: you can use this to render a complete video in multible steps. set it to increment, reset the counter to 0. in the comfyui panel activate extra options and increase the batch count. the video info node will show how many frames your video has. you dont't have to calculate exaclty here. it will only load the available frames. e.g. 550 frames, load-cap = 200, batch count = 3 would be 600 frames.

nodes.title: Load-Cap + Overlap
widgets_values: a + b if c == 0 else a + b

###never use mute, otherwise the workflow will no longer work.

images, models etc. are passed through the groups if one of the groups in between has been muted, the groups behind it no longer work.

Set VAE Encode to yes in the first KSamper to use the loaded images as referece and use a denoise value of e.g. 0.5, if you want to use a empty latent set it to no and use a denoise value of 1.0

the 2nd sampler has now the option to use an upscale model which you can choose in the node above. 

the scale_by value acts as a downscale in this case because the upscale model will upscale every image in you batch to e.g. 4x. 
scale_by is used to calculate the new size by using the image size before upscale and increases it by e.g. 1.5 
(512x912 x 1.5 -> 768x1368).

i've added a purge node after the downscale and a vae encode batched that might help to finish the 2nd pass but if you run oom or the system hangs lower the scale_by value, reduce the number of images in your batch or disable this option.

For tests a load-cap of min 16 is recommended because the context length is 16 and context_overlap is 4 by default. if you go lower the image quality will be bad e.g. tests with 2 images.

You can setup the Frame Rate in the Node above (important for image sequences) or set 'Use Video Framerate' in the Input Video Group to 'yes' to overwrite this setting.

###Adaptive Denoise When adaptive\_denoise\_steps in the Animatediff group is enabled, the steps are calculated by using the amount of steps (Sampler Settings) and the denoise value (BasicScheduler).

e.g. 10 steps + denoise 0.5 = 5 steps.

increase the step number if you want to do more steps or disable this feature.

###Create a Video from Images - Bypass the ControlNet Groups - Bypass Prompt - Bypass AnimateDiff - Bypass both KSamplers

This allows you to load a video or images and send them directly to Face Restore or, if this group is also bypassed, to Video Combine.

Use Input Audio to add a different audio file.

enable only one of these groups:
- Input Video or
- Input Images

the new Input Audio group allows you to use a different audio file for the video and use audio for your image sequences.
